    "narrative": "For LawDog\u2019s April 25th slate, the heart of our order hinges on **Cal Raleigh** (71.30) and **Geraldo Perdomo** (68.05), who represent our strongest offensive upside. **Cal Raleigh** benefits significantly from a favorable matchup against Liberatore; his secondary catcher role is bolstered by a high xwOBA and an advantageous #2 spot in the order, providing the best floor-to-ceiling ratio of the day. Meanwhile, **Geraldo Perdomo** capitalizes on a soft pitching matchup against M\u00e1rquez; his leadoff assignment combined with the SP's high xERA (5.26) makes him a mandatory start to secure volume in runs and stolen bases. Similarly, **Jonathan Aranda** (65.19) and **Bryson Stott** (66.12) are locked in as core plays, benefiting from strong dynamic platoon advantages that inflate their efficiency scores well above their baselines.\n\nNavigating the fringes of the lineup required careful consideration of our stolen base mandate. **Jung Hoo Lee** (50.33) and **Matt Chapman** (55.93) both received a critical nudge in their scoring due to the slow delivery of Eury P\u00e9rez, which maximizes their potential to swipe bags\u2014a vital priority for this roster. The most difficult benching decision of the day was **Jeremiah Jackson** (43.63), who fell just shy of the start against Crochet. While **Jeremiah Jackson** offers intrigue, the elite skill of the opposing pitcher and the overall offensive output projections for **Daulton Varsho** and others squeezed him out; **Masyn Winn** (39.65) was also considered but ultimately fell below our 40.0 scoring floor.\n\nRisk management remains a primary concern regarding **Taylor Ward** (59.46) and **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** (59.41). Both face high-level pitching in Crochet and Gausman, respectively. While **Taylor Ward** sees a massive 16% park adjustment that maintains his score, the SP skill deficit is glaring. Similarly, while **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** is an essential anchor, his poor BvP history against Gausman acts as a slight drag on an otherwise elite baseline. We are proceeding with this lineup but will monitor weather developments and any late-breaking changes to confirmed lineups for **Wenceel Perez** or other lower-order bats.",
